__WORDSIZE as defined by <stdint.h> is broken for C++ without __STDC_LIMIT_MACROS. I'm going to blame base r228529 for the issue here.

# Test for 10.3 or 11.0 amd64
$ cat >a.cc
#include <stdint.h>
#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    printf("%d\n", __WORDSIZE);
    return 0;
}

$ c++ a.cc
$ ./a.out
32
